<br>
I really think it's just a matter of skill. A really good tank knows what he has to do to control the fight and get the most out of his group. He is the one that will keep the mobs back to the pet, use groupmates to assist in pulls I.E. asking the ranger / druid to harmony a mob he can't possibly single pull,and never dies from enrage.<br>
<br>
The tank that lacks skill or simply doesn't care is the one that always overpulls or pulls when group is OOM, doesn't care where mob is positioned for pets or rangers using bows and seems to go AFK while tanking a mob alot.<br>
<br>
I have met ALOT of great tanks that have done their best to keep my water pet happily backstabbing. But the majority of them think that they are simply there to keep the cleric busy with Cheals.<br>
<br>
On a side note I recently had the priviledge of being in a inner cave group with a tank that was in my defination &quot;awesome&quot;.<br>
I wish I can remember his name off the top of my head cause I would plug him =) When I got there the first thing he asked me was &quot;what pet are you using?&quot; I told him my new water pet. He said &quot;great I'll keep the mobs backs to him&quot;. Soon afterwards we got a really good ranger with endless quiver and such and the tank kept the mob in position so pet could backstab and ranger could stick it without having to keep moving.<br>
<br>
Yeah I believe there is more skill to tanking than just being a meatsheild and waiting for the &quot;bash&quot; button to refresh <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234133">Ghetto_and_Proud</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tuis>Tuis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 3:42:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8003.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.elp.rr.com/scythek/everquest/Tuis.JPG height=120 width=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Steel Warrior post .. Comments?</span><hr size=1> I usually don't ask, but tanks I group with pick it up eventually. <p><a href="http://home.elp.rr.com/scythek/everquest/">Tuis Kagato</a> - Arch Convoker of Karana (<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=175764">Profile</a>) - <a href="http://www.pandemonium.cc/">Deloth's Dudes</a><br>
